description: What do all these women have in common?: Mariah Carey, Madonna, Celine Dion, Alanis Morissette, Carole King, Whitney Houston & Shania Twain - they are the only women to have sold over 9 million RIAA certified copies of an album! Shania's the Woman in Me contains 12 tracks (8 of which became singles); the album is nearing diamond status, with 10 million units in the U.S. alone. Come on Over contains 16 new songs; the 1st single/video "Love Gets Me Every Time," to be followed up by "Don't Be Stupid (You Know I Love You)."
